<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/14894080-dolly"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1353851751i/14894080._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/14894080-dolly">Dolly</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I agree it is wordy and more like a reading assignment in a Philosophy course at the beginning. But as soon as the Ozu character is introduced, you be<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I agree it is wordy and more like a reading assignment in a Philosophy course at the beginning. But as soon as the Ozu character is introduced, you begin to love the three main characters. It's worth staying with it to the end. Listening to an audio version helps, while reading along in the book. Hearing the narrator's voice endears her to you. Stay with it. It's a beautiful book in many ways.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
