    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1606315944" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1606315944" />
    <a title="Deea" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8111258-deea"><img alt="Deea" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1634726709p2/8111258.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1606315944?book_show_action=true">Apr 10, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Deea" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Deea" href="/user/show/8111258-deea">Deea</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Deea by: </span>
      Books, tea &amp; more. Club de carte lunar.
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8111258-deea?shelf=best-2016">best-2016</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8111258-deea?shelf=favourites">favourites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1606315944" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13213695046145585981">“All it takes is one experience of being blind in broad daylight and able to see in pitch dark to wonder what sight is all about.” Indeed after you read this book, you feel that you can be blind even if your sight is alright.<br/><br/>I really liked the philosophy which is so present in its pages. It talks about loneliness, about how past dramas can put a print on our whole lives, about how much encountering someone whom we click with can change our whole existence. It talks about love, about genuine feel</span>
  <span id="freeText13213695046145585981" style="display:none">“All it takes is one experience of being blind in broad daylight and able to see in pitch dark to wonder what sight is all about.” Indeed after you read this book, you feel that you can be blind even if your sight is alright.<br /><br />I really liked the philosophy which is so present in its pages. It talks about loneliness, about how past dramas can put a print on our whole lives, about how much encountering someone whom we click with can change our whole existence. It talks about love, about genuine feelings, about kindred souls, about how we perceive people taking into account their social status and finances. Full of gems and wit, it quite impressed me and I would like to recommend it to anyone in need of a book which can determine us to question life itself.<br /><br />This book is about time and how it can have different valences when you experience love, how it can flow differently when you discover something that you like and you get out of the daily routine. It talks about literature and music, therefore about art and how it can embrace our lives and embellish our special moments, make them seem out of this world. It talks radiantly about beauty. About beauty and ugliness, happiness and sadness.<br /><br />“…maybe that’s what life is about: there’s a lot of despair, but also the odd moment of beauty, where time is no longer the same. It's as if those strains of music created a sort of interlude in time, something suspended, an elsewhere that had come to us, an always within never.”<br /><br />This book taught me that “art is life, playing to other rhythms”. While reading it, I got so immersed in those other rhythms that although it’s been a week since I have finished it, its mysterious effects still linger on my soul.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="13213695046145585981" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


